r as frank recalled his early discussions with muncies town leaders there was nothing about the town that particularly appealed to me but the men were all courteous kind and businesslike frank agreed to a proposal that offered the ball brothers  acres  hectares of land for a factory site a gas well and  in cash to encourage the move to muncie in addition city officials agreed to provide a railroad connection to the brothers new facilities by september  construction had begun on the muncie factory and the ball brothers began plans to relocate their glass manufacturing operations from new york frank remained in muncie to get the factory up and running while edmund closed the glass factory in buffalo then moved to muncie to join frank their brothers william and george remained in buffalo to operate the stamping works and a factory in bath new york in  the company opened its first glass manufacturing facility in muncie on february  fires were started in the new factorys furnace on march  its first glass products were made the first products to be manufactured in the new factory in muncie were oil containers and lamp chimneys not fruit jars by  the ball companys headquarters and its glass and metal manufacturing operations had relocated to muncie the other ball brothers moved to indiana in the s george relocated to muncie in  william arrived in  and lucius a company shareholder and a physician moved to muncie in  in the late nineteenth century the company continued to grow and prosper but not without experiencing some challenges fires at its muncie factories and warehouses in  and  damaged its facilities but they were rebuilt despite the economic panic of  the company was able to produce  million fruit jars for the year beginning in september  and  million jars by  when natural gas supplies in the area began to diminish the ball brothers installed gas converters to use indiana coal in their factories and continued manufacturing operations the companys f c ball machine patented in  introduced mass production into its glassblowing process and gave it a competitive market advantage by  the company was producing  million canning jars per year and had acquired other glass manufacturers expanding its operations to include seven factories in addition to its main facilities at muncie in a continuation of the companys difficulties in muncie workers organized with local  glass workers of the industrial workers of the world iww at the main facility went on strike in march  with the strikers demanding wage increases a settlement was quickly reached on march  but company management reneged on the agreement and threatened to declare a lockout the strike continued but was weakened by the refusal of machinists affiliated with the american federation of labor to join the strike by the end of april the strike was lost diversificationedit ball remained a familyowned business for more than ninety years renamed the ball brothers company in  it is best known for manufacturing fruit jars lids and related products for home canning the company also entered into other business ventures because the four main components of their core product line of canning jars included glass zinc rubber and paper the ball company acquired a zinc strip rolling mill to produce metal lids for their glass jars manufactured rubber sealing rings for the jars and acquired a paper mill to fabricate the packaging used in shipping their products the company also acquired tin steel and later plastic companies the ball company faced additional challenges and opportunities during the great depression and world war ii prior to  ball was the largest domestic manufacturer of home canning jars in  it manufactured  percent of all the canning jars made in the united states however a drop in demand for the jars during the s led the ball brothers to begin manufacturing other types of jars and bottles for commercial use and expand into other lines of business during world war ii the companys operations were converted to produce shells and machine parts for the military after the war balls glassmaking business was hindered by an antitrust case in which the company was one of several defendants the legal case was appealed to the us supreme court the final decision which was handed down in  restricted balls ability to acquire other glass manufacturers and other businesses producing glassmaking machinery without prior court approval in  the decreasing demand for canning jars caused the company to suffer its first net operating loss with legal restrictions on the companys ability to expand its glassmaking business and declining demand for its canning jars ball company executives decided that in order to grow it had to further diversity its holdings in the s the ball company entered the aerospace industry laboratories for the ball brothers research corporation were established at boulder colorado and in muncie the company began manufacturing aerospace equipment in  its oso orbiting solar observatory satellite designed and built for the national aeronautics and space administration nasa with  million in grants launched into space on march   at cape canaveral florida its success led to additional contracts to build more satellites a total of seven but not without some losses an explosion killed three workers and damaged the companys oso satellite in  the company continued to expand into other areas such as avionics aerospace systems and metal beverage and food containers renamed the ball corporation in  it acquired jeffco manufacturing company a maker of recyclable aluminum beverage cans and became the largest producer of recyclable beverage cans in the world although glass production in muncie ceased in  it continued at other ball plants until its final until its final glass manufacturing operations were sold in  ball corporations stock went public on july  citation needed it became a publiclytraded stock company on the new york stock exchange in  the stock began trading at  per share on the nyse on december   using the trading symbol bllcitation needed ball no longer produces its glass canning jars in the early s ball exited the homecanning business when it established a subsidiary named alltrista which consisted of seven smaller ball subsidiaries that included the ball jar and other canningrelated products when altrista corporation became a separate company in april  ball shareholders received one share of alltrista stock for every four shares of ball stock altrista was renamed jarden corporation in  jarden retains the license to use the ball registered trademark on its line of homecanning products a part of jardens branded consumables business jarden produces lids for several brands of fruit jars at its muncie plant and its jars are made by a variety of glass producerscitation needed in  the ball corporation moved its corporate headquarters from muncie to broomfield colorado where its oversees global operations as a manufacturer of plastic and metal food and beverage containers as well as a manufacturer of equipment and supplier of services to the aerospace industry company milestonesedit  frank and edmund ball acquired the wood jacket can company the predecessor to the ball corporation in buffalo new york  incorporated as ball brothers glass manufacturing company  a new glass factory was built in muncie indiana metal manufacturing operations continued at buffalo and bath new york  the companys metal fittings operations were moved to muncie  f c ball machine the worlds first semiautomatic glass machine was invented us patent number  issued in   the correct method for preserving fruit predecessor to the ball blue book was published it featured homecanning recipes and techniques  name changed to ball brothers company  fire causes  in damages to balls glass plant number one in muncie  ball formed ball brothers research corporation to produce goods and services for the aerospace sector this was converted to a wholly owned subsidiary ball aerospace  technologies corp in   ball purchased industrial rubber of st joseph mi which was later sold to chardon rubber in   balls muncie glass plant is closed  company name is changed to the ball corporation  ball became a publiclytraded stock listed on new york stock exchange  alltrista a ball subsidiary was spun off into a separate corporation renamed the jarden corporation in  it uses of the ball registered trademark on its line of homecanning products  ball began manufacturing pet plastic containers  ball created ballfoster glass container co a joint venture glass company with saintgobain  ball exited the glass business selling its interests in ballfoster to saintgobain  corporate headquarters relocated from muncie indiana to broomfield colorado  ball acquired schmalbachlubeca ag the germanbased metal beverage container company and created ball packaging europe  ball celebrated its th anniversary  ball acquired us can inc the largest us manufacturer of aerosol cans  ball corporation issued its first sustainability report  ball acquired aerocan sas makers of aluminum aerosol cans and bottles for  million  ball acquired rexam a uk based packaging company major subsidiariesedit ball aerospace  technologies corp ball packaging europe environmental recordedit the ball corporation has made improvements to its environmental record since  when the company began its first formal sustainability efforts in  the ball corporation issued its first sustainability report and began releases subsequent sustainability reports on its website the first report was an accaceres north american sustainability awards cowinner of the best first time reporter award in citation needed in the toxic  list for  using data from  researchers at the university of massachusetts amhersts political economy research institute peri identified the ball corporation as the thlargest corporate producer of air pollution in the united states with an estimated  million pounds of toxic air released annually the peri report for  using data from  ranked the ball corporation th on its toxic  list peris report for  using data from  ranked it th the peri studies indicated major pollutants included glycol ethers and trimethylbenzene the peri toxic  air polluters list for  ranked the ball corporation as  in its list of companies producing the most air pollution in the united states in  newsweek ranked the ball corporation as th in their green  report which reviewed the environmental performances of the  largest publiclytraded companies in the united states notesedit  a b c d e f g ball corporation form k annual report filing date feb   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved feb     ball corporation form k annual report filing date apr   secdatabasecom retrieved feb     a b c d e f g h i j k l barbara quigley the ball brothers in gugin linda c james e st clair eds  indianas  the people who shaped the hoosier state indianapolis indiana historical society press p  isbn    anthony o edmonds e bruce geelhoed  ball state university an interpretive history bloomington in indiana university press p  isbn    philip a africa  keuka college a history valley forge pa judson press pp – oclc    frank clayton ball  memoirs of frank clayton ball muncie in scott printing company pp – oclc    edmund f ball  from fruit jars to satellites the story of ball brothers company incorporated new york necomen society in north america p    ball memoirs of frank clayton ball pp –  frederic a birmingham  ball corporation the first century indianapolis in curtis publishing company p  isbn    birmingham pp –  william f brantley  a collectors guide to ball jars muncie in rosemary humbert martin p  oclc    a b birmingham p   ball memoirs of frank clayton ball pp –  ball memoirs of frank clayton ball p   ball memoirs of frank clayton ball p   ball memoirs of frank clayton ball p   ball memoirs of frank clayton ball pp –  edmonds and geelhoed pp –  a b c ray boomhower winter  destination indiana oakhurst 